docs.lead_paragraph: Except for a reaction in sterling, the Scandinavians and the guilder, other foreign currencies developed a moderately higher trend last week. The franc of France and Switzerland, lire, belga and Central Europeans showed an advance ranging from a fraction to 6 points. The intrusion of the holiday and the cautious attitude of banks and traders awaiting the gold-clause decision resulted in a moderate turnover throughout the week.

docs.lead_paragraph: Chief interest in the foreign exchanges last week centred in the demoralized state of the market on Monday following the Supreme Court's decision in the gold-clause suits. Sharp advances were recorded in all currencies. Sterling rose 2 1/8 cents, French francs 3 3/8 points, guilders 42 points. Swiss francs 20 points and the belga 14 points. Measurably large gains were also reported in other continentals.
